

# CoreQuarry Architectural Blueprint: Unified Index Label Bitmasking

## 1. Executive Summary & Design Pivot

In earlier iterations of CoreQuarry's hybrid knowledge engine, structural mapping designs attempted to compress structural syntax paths (such as hierarchical file nodes, XML brackets, or JSON tree positions) directly into the upper bits of a 64-bit scalar label inside the Hierarchical Navigable Small World (HNSW) vector index. 

This approach has been deprecated due to a fundamental behavioral trait of dense vector spaces: **hierarchical structural taxonomy does not map linearly to multi-dimensional semantic space.** Identical or highly similar prose blocks (e.g., `"Set the context variable to null"`) routinely appear across structurally divergent sections of technical datasets (e.g., getting-started guides, API specifications, and troubleshooting code appendices). Forcing structural taxonomy flags into dense graph identifiers fragments graph traversal routing and yields no index-level optimization.

To construct a hardware-sympathetic engine ready for production workloads, CoreQuarry repurposes the upper bits of the 64-bit scalar space. Instead of tracking *where* an asset lives structurally, **the upper 24 bits are reserved for an in-flight categorical binary bitmask filter.** This leaves a massive 40-bit address space for unique record identifiers—supporting up to 1+ trillion unique vector nodes per index instance while enabling blisteringly fast, single-instruction bitwise pruning directly within the graph traversal loop.

---

## 2. Memory Layout Allocation

By embedding critical categorical metadata directly inside the HNSW scalar label, CoreQuarry completely eliminates pointer chasing, hash-map lookups, and secondary relational tracking table joins during the initial graph traversal phase. Data remains fully localized within the CPU's L1/L2 cache lines during proximity scoring.


<PRE>
64-Bit Unified Scalar Label Layout:
┌───────────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┐
│       24-Bit Metadata Bitmask         │        40-Bit Dense Vector ID         │
│     (Upper Bits: 40 to 63)            │         (Lower Bits: 0 to 39)         │
├───────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────┤
│ 00000000 00000000 00000000            │ 00000000 00000000 ... 0000000000000001│
└───────────────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────────┘
▲                                       ▲
│                                       │
└── Category Flags, Visibility Controls, └── Flat Identifier Map to Lexical Object
and Linguistic Locales                  Store (~1.09 Trillion Capacity)
